==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immanency
<hw>Im"ma*nen*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The condition or quality of
being immanent; inherence; an indwelling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Clement] is mainly concerned in enforcing the
<qex>immanence</qex> of God. Christ is everywhere presented by him as
Deity indwelling in the world.</q> <rj><qau>A. V. G.
Allen.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immanent</ent>⟦br⟧
